body:
I tried running this code with Miri ([on playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?edition=2018&gist=a4554cb559927e74ce71f75af1ba1d45)):

```rust
fn test_all_refs<'a, T: 'a>(dummy: &mut T, iter: impl Iterator<Item = &'a mut T>) {
    // Gather all those references.
    let mut refs: Vec<&mut T> = iter.collect();
    // Use them all. Twice, to be sure we got all interleavings.
    for r in refs.iter_mut() {
        std::mem::swap(dummy, r);
    }
    for r in refs {
        std::mem::swap(dummy, r);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let mut v = std::collections::VecDeque::new();
    v.push_back(1);
    v.push_back(2);
    test_all_refs(&mut 0, v.iter_mut());
}
```

I expected to see it end gracefully.

